content: I was honestly going to give this at least a 3-star rating but then I found out it's 100% sexist. Women get the whole of the app completely free, men are charged a high monthly fee for any additional features. I'm sure I'll be judged a chauvinist pig for this but as much as I agree women need to feel safe on dating apps, the cost shouldn't solely come out of the men's wallets... So before I found that out, I was going to say it isn't a badly designed app, but it is (ironically) let down by the user base and the dev's choice of advertising. A good 50% are either spam accounts or the person just hasn't bothered filling their profile out with most of them just writing "ask me" if they even write anything at all. If you're a guy you are penalised by the fact that you can't click on any of the features without a full screen advert for VIP membership taking over, or an obnoxiously loud full screen advert for some 3rd party company. You can't make use of the free VIP trial without handing over your banking details (it says you can cancel but honestly when has that EVER been hassle free...) Positives are: Nice layout and design, it's good that you can actually see how far away people are so you aren't wasting your time, and the concept of revealing people by chatting is fresh and interesting.
